        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 8:59AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 859 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Talladega National Forest to 7 miles north
of Potter Station to 7 miles southeast of Central Mills. Movement was
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lomax, Dollar, Gap Of The Mountain, Bogue Chitto, Stanton,
Carlowville, Robert F. Henry Lock And Dam, Parnell, Clanton, Tyler, I
65 Rest Area, Selma, Craig Field Aiport, Plantersville, Dannelly
Reservoir, Verbena, Randolph, Selmont-West Selmont, Mulberry, and
Marbury.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for central,
south central and east central Alabama.</instruction>
